---
title: Zucchini Pomodoro Penne Bake with Mozzarella & Herbed Ricotta
description: No matter the weather, it’s pretty much impossible not to daydream about cheesy baked carbs. Luckily, this dish is guaranteed to make those dreams come true. In it, you’ll find penne and zucchini layered with herby, creamy ricotta and a rich marinara sauce. To top things off, there’s a melty blanket of mozzarella. Serve it right from the dish for maximum cheese pull potential and wait for the oohs and aahs from your lucky fellow diners.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/61cb2c09813874009620da38-4168f376.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/zucchini-pomodoro-penne-bake-61cb2c09813874009620da38-1380d435.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/zucchini-pomodoro-penne-bake-61cb2c09813874009620da38
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 770 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 100 g
  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 960 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 45 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{}ed water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice half the @yellow onion{1} (whole onion for 4 servings). Finely dice @roma tomato{1}. Trim @zucchini{1}, then grate on the largest holes of a #box grater{}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until almost al dente, ~{8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in step 6).

Drain penne. (Keep empty pot handy for step 5.)

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add diced onion, tomato, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @marinara{14%ounce%cup}, zucchini, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), @water{1/4%cup} (½ cup for 4), @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4), and a big pinch of salt. (You'll use more Italian Seasoning in the next step.) Bring to a simmer; cook, stirring, ~{3%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

While sauce simmers, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{1%ounce}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and a drizzle of @olive oil{}. (Use the rest of the Italian Seasoning as you like.) Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add drained penne, sauce, and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) to pot used for pasta. Season with salt and pepper; stir to thoroughly combine.

Spread out half the pasta mixture in an 8-by-8-inch #baking dish{}. (For 4, use a 9-by-13-inch baking dish.) Using a #tablespoon{}, dollop pasta mixture with herbed ricotta. Top with remaining pasta mixture, then sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Cover baking dish with #foil{}. (TIP: Coat inside of foil with nonstick spray first to prevent sticking.) Bake pasta on top rack for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from oven; discard foil.

Heat broiler to high. Broil until cheese is lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let cool slightly; top with @?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} if desired. Divide between plates and serve.